    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Veneer made from tree excrescences that are typically in the form of flattened hemispheres. For example, one type of burl veneer is made from the stumps of walnut trees.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
